import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    """The Capacity Ratio and Inverse Log Score Algorithm calculates the scores as the capacity ratio between the item size and the rest capacity of the bins, 
    further adjusted by the inverse logarithms of the rest capacities."""

    # Calculate the capacity ratio between the item size and the rest capacity of the bins
    capacity_ratio = item / bins
    
    # Adjust the capacity ratio by taking the inverse logarithms of the rest capacities
    inverse_log_scores = 1 / np.log(1 + bins)
    
    # Calculate the scores as the product of the capacity ratio and the inverse log scores
    scores = capacity_ratio * inverse_log_scores
    
    return scores
